There are plenty of nicer things to buy with your money. They are the
horological equivalent of Beanie babies.

Interestingly enough these clocks with the works removed and replaced
with a battery movement seem to sell as easily for not much less money.

Most colleges of further education run clock repairing evening courses
whereby you take a broken clock in and over a course of weeks clean/fix
it yourself under the supervision of someone with greasy hair, bad teeth
and a clothes sense that ended in 1954. This is the course of action I
would recommend to the O.P.
--
Colonel Blink The Short Sighted Gink
(Not just any Pop, Dick or Harry.)

