"/> As you know Ronnie, I'm not trade. But the price I pay for a
Westminster is twice that of a simple strike. I'm buying them as
scrappers, to provide mechanisms for a newly built case. They normally
need cleaning, which I do myself, but anything more than that I send
out. Like stained glass work, there are other crafts people needing
work and I'd rather hand off the stuff that isn't quite my line - I
get cabinetry coming back my way.

My lounge clock at the moment is a Perivale (so one notch up from a
Smiths). Perfectly ordinary, but well proportioned, walnut veneer case
- cost me twenty quid from the Oxfam shop in Bath. In the workshop is
a plug-ugly modern Kieninger, balance wheel and chime, in an all glass
case - 45 quid. Don't know what I'll do with it in the end, but that
mechanism would cost me 250 new.

